betterquesting:10.desc:8:
I can only imagine all of the horrible things that may have happened to my potato, but I have bigger fish to fry. I need to get out of this place, whatever it is. 

When I look closely, I notice that there seems to be a small patch on what must be the ceiling that looks different than the rest of this dark room. Maybe it's a vent or something. I should try interacting with it to see if it does anything. (shift+left-click with an empty hand)

This whole place smells like it could go up in flames at any moment with the smallest spark. For lack of a better idea i'm going to just (SLOWLY) punch the ground below me until something happens. If the entire place goes up in flames and this is how my life ends, well, we had a good run. 

Just maybe, though, it will be only enough to start a small fire that I can throw my little pebbles into to see if anything happens. Sounds rediculous doesn't it? It's not like I have any better ideas.

For all my troubles, all I got was some bigger stones (this place is weird). These won't do me any good, and I can't find anything else that could possibly be useful. I knew it was hopeless. I don't want to just sit here until I die, I want to go out on my own terms... (stay in a fire for to long)

Great, now I can break this big chunk of my old skull down into smaller bones (break with fists). Once I do that I can rig something together with these bones and that stone from earlier. That just might be strong enough to break me out of here. 

§o(To craft a bone pickaxe, open your inventory, click either your bones or cobblestone, then hold shift, drag it on top of the ingredient that you didn't pick up, and click again)

I'm free! Well, not really. I escaped the dark room I woke up in only to discover that i'm stuck in some sort of empty void. On the plus side, this ability to start fires wherever I want is proving to be quite handy. I should keep lighting different things on fire to see where it takes me.

§o(Burn Bones to get bone torches. Place a cobblestone on top of the bedrock (the top site of the bedrock) and light it with the bone torch (leftclick). Now you have charred cobblestone. Mine the charred cobblestone to acquire gravel.)

if you burn gravel in fire you get flint, craft it with a sharped bone to create a flint knife, which can be used to cut yourself and get more food out of yourself. use 8 raw player meat on a charred cobblestone, which is placed on bedrock to obtain a flesh block, which you can transform into dirt later.
apply 4 bone meal to a flesh block that is placed on bedrock to transform it into dirt.

Unlock the "wood" stage by purchasing the research in the research menu (use the book to open the GUI) after that you can rightclick a dirt block with a piece of bine meal which is placed on bedrock to spawn a sapling.
Where am I? I uh... this uh... this can't be good. This can't be good at all. Why is it so dark? I'm not even quite sure which way is up.

Okay... I need to think back to this morning to try and figure out how I got here. Let's see now... my alarm woke me up at 7:00 a.m., I got up, took a shower, got dressed, brushed my teeth and went on my daily walk to work. Actually wait, before I left for work I grabbed a potato to eat on my lunch break.

Hmm.. i'm really hungry now, where did my potato go? I don't remember ever eating it, and it doesn't seem to be in my pockets. Where is my potato? =(

What? I'm not dead? I see my old body just laying there, but i'm standing right here in a different body. Things are making even less sense then they did before, but maybe I can take advantage of new found regeneration power of mine. Maybe if I try reducing my old body to bone I can use it for some sort of tools. The first step would be to get all of the excess material off by tossing my old head in a fire.
